<TITLE> BNP faction writes to CA for release of Khaleda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 23 (bdnews24.com)A BNP faction led by Khandaker Delwar Hossain handed a letter to the Chief Adviser's Office Sunday, with appeals for the release of Khaleda Zia and her sons Tarique Rahman and Arafat Rahman Coco before Independence Day. BNP's acting office secretary Rizvi Ahmed carried the letter signed by BNP standing committee member Dr RA Ghani to the Chief Adviser's Office. "The letter was handed over to the officials at the CA's office at 12:40pm. The two-page letter written on the party letterhead demanded the release of all political prisoners, including Khaleda Zia by March 26." The decision on demand for the release of "political prisoners" by writing a letter to the CA was taken at a meeting of the senior leaders of BNP and its front organisations Thursday. bdnew
